{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0159WyRFyzRPNnK9nC5fbiZZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Progress Log\n     2→\n     3→This file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\n     4→after each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n     5→\n     6→## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n     7→\n     8→- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n     9→- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n    10→- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n    11→- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n    12→- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n    13→\n    14→---\n    15→\n    16→## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n    17→- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n    18→- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n    19→- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n    20→- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n    21→- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n    22→- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n    23→- **Files changed:**\n    24→  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n    25→  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n    26→  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n    27→  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n    28→  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n    29→  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n    30→  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n    31→  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n    32→  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n    33→- **Learnings:**\n    34→  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n    35→  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n    36→  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n    37→  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n    38→  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n    39→---\n    40→\n    41→## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n    42→- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n    43→- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n    44→- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n    45→- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n    46→- **Files changed:**\n    47→  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n    48→  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n    49→- **Learnings:**\n    50→  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n    51→  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n    52→---\n    53→\n    54→## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n    55→- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n    56→- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n    57→- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n    58→- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n    59→- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n    60→- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n    61→- **Files changed:**\n    62→  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n    63→  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n    64→  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n    65→- **Learnings:**\n    66→  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n    67→  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n    68→  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n    69→  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n    70→  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n    71→---\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d56355a6-bacd-4370-b1eb-287b8a057da0","uuid":"3923cbf2-7041-4977-a31f-bf48ad21941d","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","content":"# Ralph Progress Log\n\nThis file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\nafter each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n\n## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n- **Learnings:**\n  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n","numLines":72,"startLine":1,"totalLines":72}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KQj9PZgB3dpq7gc29SP3Yy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01S4EP5PWSihaUENstnpZiMG","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","old_string":"  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---","new_string":"  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5\n- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`\n- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input\n- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression\n- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)\n- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output\n- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression\n- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression\n- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages\n- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset\n- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)\n- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage\n- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states\n  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg\n  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper\n  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)\n  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg\n  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget\n  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes\n  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result\n---"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1768,"cache_read_input_tokens":48480,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1768},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d56355a6-bacd-4370-b1eb-287b8a057da0","uuid":"a4eee29c-9c5f-4b71-beee-02b2cece8bd5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S4EP5PWSihaUENstnpZiMG","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d56355a6-bacd-4370-b1eb-287b8a057da0","uuid":"6713187a-22de-4083-ad7b-5cbfd24490bb","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/home/jorgecevallos/Documents/web-video/.ralph-tui/progress.md","oldString":"  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---","newString":"  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5\n- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`\n- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input\n- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression\n- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)\n- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output\n- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression\n- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression\n- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages\n- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset\n- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)\n- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage\n- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states\n  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression\n  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg\n  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency\n- **Learnings:**\n  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper\n  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)\n  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg\n  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget\n  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes\n  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result\n---","originalFile":"# Ralph Progress Log\n\nThis file tracks progress across iterations. Agents update this file\nafter each iteration and it's included in prompts for context.\n\n## Codebase Patterns (Study These First)\n\n- **Next.js 16 + ESLint**: `next lint` CLI command was removed in Next.js 16. Use `eslint .` directly with flat config. `eslint-config-next@16` exports a flat config array natively — no need for `@eslint/eslintrc` FlatCompat wrapper.\n- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Uses `@import \"tailwindcss\"` and `@theme {}` blocks in CSS instead of `tailwind.config.js`. Custom colors defined via `--color-*` CSS variables in `@theme`.\n- **Custom colors**: Access via `text-text-primary`, `bg-background`, `bg-accent`, etc. (Tailwind v4 maps `--color-*` to utility classes automatically).\n- **Font**: Inter loaded via `next/font/google` with `variable: \"--font-inter\"`, applied to `<html>` class. CSS uses `--font-sans` in `@theme` block.\n- **Package manager**: pnpm installed at `$HOME/.local/bin/pnpm` (nix store is read-only). Always `export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"` before pnpm commands.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.1\n- Initialized Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind CSS v4, ESLint 9\n- Configured dark theme with custom color palette (background #0a0a0a, surface #141414, accent purple #6d28d9)\n- Set up Inter font via next/font/google\n- Created base layout (app/layout.tsx) with dark background, text colors, and antialiased rendering\n- Created placeholder home page (app/page.tsx) with hero-like content\n- Created folder structure: app/, components/, lib/\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `package.json` - scripts, dependencies\n  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript config (auto-updated by Next.js)\n  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js config\n  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS with @tailwindcss/postcss\n  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint flat config with eslint-config-next\n  - `app/globals.css` - Tailwind v4 theme with custom dark colors\n  - `app/layout.tsx` - Root layout with Inter font and dark theme\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Home page placeholder\n  - `.gitignore` - Standard Next.js gitignore\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Next.js 16 removed the `next lint` CLI command; use `eslint .` directly\n  - `eslint-config-next@16` exports flat config natively, no FlatCompat needed\n  - Tailwind CSS v4 uses `@theme {}` blocks instead of `tailwind.config.js`\n  - pnpm can't be installed globally in nix — use `--prefix=$HOME/.local`\n  - `create-next-app` refuses to run in non-empty directories; manual setup is more reliable\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.2\n- Created Hero section component (`components/Hero.tsx`) with title, accent-colored keyword, subtitle, and CTA button\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to import and render the Hero component with a `#compresor` anchor placeholder\n- Hero is fully responsive (text scales from `text-4xl` on mobile to `text-6xl` on desktop)\n- CTA button uses `<a href=\"#compresor\">` to scroll to the future compressor section\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/Hero.tsx` - New Hero section component\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Updated to use Hero component\n- **Learnings:**\n  - The `@/` path alias works out of the box with Next.js 16 + TypeScript for importing from project root\n  - Using `text-accent-light` for keyword emphasis works well with the existing theme palette\n---\n\n## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.4\n- Created `VideoUpload` component (`components/VideoUpload.tsx`) with drag & drop and click-to-select functionality\n- Component validates file types against both MIME types and file extensions for robustness\n- Displays file name, size (formatted), and format after selection\n- Error message shown when non-video file is selected\n- Created `CompressorSection` wrapper component (`components/CompressorSection.tsx`) as client component to manage upload state\n- Updated `app/page.tsx` to replace placeholder anchor with `CompressorSection`\n- **Files changed:**\n  - `components/VideoUpload.tsx` - New video upload component with drag & drop\n  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - New client wrapper for the compressor section\n  - `app/page.tsx` - Replaced placeholder anchor with CompressorSection\n- **Learnings:**\n  - Client components (`\"use client\"`) are needed for drag & drop and file input state management in Next.js App Router\n  - Wrapping interactive sections in a dedicated client component (CompressorSection) keeps the page.tsx as a server component\n  - The `SelectedFile` interface is exported for reuse by future components (US-005 compression input)\n  - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box\n  - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format\n---\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":69,"oldLines":3,"newStart":69,"newLines":30,"lines":["   - Tailwind v4 custom colors work with opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-accent/10`, `bg-accent/15`) out of the box","   - Dual validation (MIME type + extension) handles edge cases where browsers report different MIME types for the same format"," ---","+","+## 2026-02-17 - web-video-l39.5","+- Added target size input (MB) with validation to `CompressorSection`","+- Validations: minimum 1 MB, must be less than original file size, numeric input","+- Created API route `app/api/compress/route.ts` using `fluent-ffmpeg` for server-side compression","+- API route calculates video bitrate from target size and video duration (reserves 128kbps for audio)","+- Compression uses single-pass encoding with `-movflags +faststart` for web-optimized output","+- Added spinner animation on compress button during compression","+- Added animated progress bar indicator during compression","+- Error state with retry button and descriptive error messages","+- Success state shows compressed size vs original, download button, and \"compress another\" reset","+- Download generates descriptive filename (e.g., `video_compressed_9.00mb.mp4`)","+- Configured `next.config.ts` with `serverExternalPackages: [\"fluent-ffmpeg\"]` for proper server-side usage","+- Installed `fluent-ffmpeg` + `@types/fluent-ffmpeg` dependencies","+- **Files changed:**","+  - `components/CompressorSection.tsx` - Added target size input, compress button, progress, error/success states","+  - `app/api/compress/route.ts` - New API route for server-side FFmpeg compression","+  - `next.config.ts` - Added `serverExternalPackages` for fluent-ffmpeg","+  - `package.json` - Added fluent-ffmpeg dependency and @types/fluent-ffmpeg dev dependency","+- **Learnings:**","+  - `fluent-ffmpeg` is deprecated but still functional; it's the most common Node.js FFmpeg wrapper","+  - Next.js App Router API routes use `formData()` on the request to handle file uploads natively (no body-parser config needed)","+  - `serverExternalPackages` in next.config.ts is needed to prevent Next.js from bundling native/CLI-dependent packages like fluent-ffmpeg","+  - Bitrate calculation: `videoBitrate = (targetSizeBytes * 8 - audioBitrate * duration) / duration` — must subtract audio bits from total budget","+  - Streaming response with `ReadableStream` from `createReadStream` works well for returning large files from API routes","+  - Custom headers like `X-Compressed-Size` can be read client-side from `response.headers.get()` for metadata about the result","+---"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
